OL,3,C'One in four councils could lose
OL,4,Cmoney' under Government's funding
OL,5,Cproposals
OL,7,FWhitehall will provide a minimum level
OL,8,Fof funding, a so-called funding floor,
OL,9,Ffor council leaders during the
OL,10,Fchanges, but the IFS said overall cash
OL,11,Ffor inner London town halls would be
OL,12,F11-12% lower in 2028-29 in real terms.
OL,14,FThe paper said: "Around one in four
OL,15,Fcouncils would see real-terms falls in
OL,16,Foverall funding under the Government's
OL,17,Fproposals, with around 30 on the
OL,18,Flowest funding floors seeing real-
OL,19,Fterms cuts of 11`12%. Conversely,
OL,20,Fanother one in four councils would see
OL,21,Freal-terms increases of 12% or more."
