OL,7,F"But the changes will sting for those
OL,8,Fcouncils that are assessed to
OL,9,Fcurrently receive too high a share of
OL,10,Fthe overall funding pot, and so which
OL,11,Flose out from moves to align funding
OL,12,Fwith assessed spending needs."
OL,14,FThe proposals are criticised in the
OL,15,Freport as "not particularly
OL,16,Fredistributive to poor, urban areas of
OL,17,FEngland". It cites South Tyneside and
OL,18,FSunderland councils being among those
OL,19,Fto lose out from the reforms as slow
OL,20,Fpopulation growth is accounted for.
